Subject: [PATCH 5/624] Add tests/harness/run-all.sh to execute all tests

Provide a new test harness script that mirrors the GUST_BIN/bootstrap
setup used by run.sh but discovers and executes every tests/t[0-9]*.sh
script unconditionally. This ensures the test suite can be run without
relying on an allowlist: the script uses find + sort to run all matching
test scripts (skipping test-lib.sh and other harness-only files), making
it easier to run the complete tests collection.
